/**
 * Salvage automation for Google Apps Script.
 *
 * What it does:
 * 1) Picks the newest Gmail message inside label QUEUED_SALVAGE that matches:
 *    - subject: "5. Replacement Claim Monitoring"
 *    - from: data-reporting@qoala.id
 *    - attachment name contains: "Replace Claim List"
 *    - attachment extension: .xlsx
 * 2) Converts the XLSX attachment into a temporary Google Spreadsheet.
 * 3) Stops immediately if duplicate Claim Number is found in the target sheet, writes a short failure notice in B1, and logs details.
 * 4) Upserts data into sheet "Salvage" on workbook "Overview Claim" based on Claim Number only.
 * 5) Marks Claim Number cells pink + adds note when an existing target claim is missing from source.
 * 6) Clears the mark/note automatically once the claim reappears in source.
 * 7) Supports a dry-run diff preview that shows what would update/insert/missing-restore before any write.
 * 8) Writes progress and detailed logs into "Log Salvage" sheet.
 * 9) Trashes the temporary spreadsheet and the processed email thread after a successful run.
 *
 * IMPORTANT SETUP:
 * - Enable Advanced Google services: Drive API, Gmail API
 * - In Apps Script project settings, set timezone to Asia/Jakarta
 * - Run setupSalvageAutomation() once manually
 *
 * BOOKMARKED NEXT IMPROVEMENTS:
 * 1) Dedicated audit columns (currently skipped by request to avoid adding more columns for now).
 * 2) Stronger source schema/structure validation so the job is more resilient if the upstream report layout changes.
 * 3) Rollback/staging write model so partial writes can be recovered more safely if a failure happens mid-write.
 */

